1
00:02:01,454 --> 00:02:02,580
Movement.

2
00:02:03,857 --> 00:02:04,949
Two men.

3
00:02:06,526 --> 00:02:07,993
Approximately

4
00:02:10,463 --> 00:02:12,226
40 goats.

5
00:02:12,332 --> 00:02:16,063
They're not on anybody's side.
We don't have to shoot them.

6
00:02:17,036 --> 00:02:18,162
Egress?

7
00:02:18,938 --> 00:02:23,739
Primary over the top, secondary
down the road, tertiary to the river.

8
00:02:25,111 --> 00:02:28,239
No one can track you through the water
except a fish.

9
00:02:38,124 --> 00:02:41,093
Sarah's headed off to nursing school
next month.

10
00:02:42,061 --> 00:02:43,653
She sewed that herself.

11
00:02:43,863 --> 00:02:45,125
It's beautiful.

12
00:02:47,233 --> 00:02:49,565
You sure this is
a peacekeeping mission?

13
00:02:50,270 --> 00:02:53,068
Normally there isn't any peace
to start with.

14
00:02:55,008 --> 00:02:57,067
This shit's awful calm.

15
00:03:09,589 --> 00:03:10,749
- Not at these coordinates.
- Yes, sir.

16
00:03:10,857 --> 00:03:12,017
Go ahead and plot an alternate.

17
00:03:12,125 --> 00:03:13,319
Yes, sir.

18
00:03:13,626 --> 00:03:16,754
Command Post, Command Post,
this is TS-129, over.

19
00:03:17,363 --> 00:03:20,491
Sir, I have visual confirmation
of TS-129's current position.

20
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:24,092
Mission accomplished, en route to
extract site. Distance eight klicks. Over.

21
00:03:24,204 --> 00:03:26,104
Command Post, Command Post,
this is Viper.

22
00:03:26,206 --> 00:03:28,538
I have friendly forces moving
towards extraction point, over.

23
00:03:30,109 --> 00:03:32,077
Heads up, our boys are coming through.

24
00:03:32,178 --> 00:03:34,009
Viper, this is CP. Be advised,

25
00:03:34,113 --> 00:03:37,480
possible hostile forces approaching
TS-129 at their 12:00.

26
00:03:37,617 --> 00:03:38,777
Call them out.

27
00:03:39,252 --> 00:03:40,219
Target.

28
00:03:41,020 --> 00:03:42,715
Sector Bravo, deep.

29
00:03:42,822 --> 00:03:45,086
Vehicle, belt-fed weapon.

30
00:03:45,191 --> 00:03:46,158
Range it.

31
00:03:50,730 --> 00:03:52,459
870 yards and closing.

32
00:03:53,399 --> 00:03:55,867
Wind, three-quarter value, push 2 left.

33
00:03:56,869 --> 00:04:00,066
900 yards. Wide spot on the road.

34
00:04:01,608 --> 00:04:02,802
On target.

35
00:04:02,909 --> 00:04:04,240
Hold scope.

36
00:04:04,344 --> 00:04:05,675
Fire when ready.

37
00:04:09,282 --> 00:04:10,306
Hit.

38
00:04:16,122 --> 00:04:19,148
Command Post, this is Viper.
Hostile threat down, over.

39
00:04:19,292 --> 00:04:22,659
Viper, this is Command Post.
We copy your traffic, over.

40
00:04:32,972 --> 00:04:35,372
Call it in. It's time to go.

41
00:04:35,475 --> 00:04:37,375
Command Post, this is Viper.
Mission accomplished.

42
00:04:37,477 --> 00:04:38,501
- Packing up.
- Shit!

43
00:04:38,611 --> 00:04:41,978
Viper, be advised larger hostile forces
approaching near sector Bravo.

44
00:04:42,081 --> 00:04:44,413
Weren't supposed to be
hostiles that close!

45
00:04:51,524 --> 00:04:55,824
Crooked tree.
675, 30 miles an hour, three-mil lead.

46
00:05:01,334 --> 00:05:04,861
Position to machine gun.
900, three-quarter value.

47
00:05:04,971 --> 00:05:06,302
Fire when ready.

48
00:05:10,710 --> 00:05:14,407
Jefe. 920. Three-quarter value.

49
00:05:14,614 --> 00:05:17,606
- I see it, Donnie. I see it.
- Fire when ready.

50
00:05:26,426 --> 00:05:28,792
- They don't know where we are.
- But they might get lucky!

51
00:05:31,197 --> 00:05:33,256
Command Post, Command Post,
this is Viper.

52
00:05:33,366 --> 00:05:35,630
Enemy forces
have been stopped. Break.

53
00:05:35,735 --> 00:05:38,465
Friendlies are continuing on
to extract point. Break.

54
00:05:38,571 --> 00:05:42,473
We're receiving small arms and
indirect fire from hostile troops. Break.

55
00:05:45,211 --> 00:05:46,644
Command Post, do you read me?

56
00:05:46,746 --> 00:05:47,974
Shut it down.

57
00:05:48,247 --> 00:05:49,214
They're highly-trained men,

58
00:05:49,315 --> 00:05:52,079
eight kilometers inside a country
we are not supposed to be in.

59
00:05:52,185 --> 00:05:54,517
I'm sure they'll get out just fine.
Shut it down now.

60
00:05:54,620 --> 00:05:56,087
Radio check. Do you read me?

61
00:05:56,189 --> 00:05:58,248
- Okay, wrap it up. Let's go!
- Do you read me?

62
00:05:58,358 --> 00:06:01,020
- Pull out those tracks.
- Pull out those tracks and pack it up!

63
00:06:12,939 --> 00:06:14,998
Intelligence said
they didn't have air support!

64
00:06:15,108 --> 00:06:16,234
Call it in!

65
00:06:19,445 --> 00:06:22,380
Shit! The channel's down!

66
00:06:22,482 --> 00:06:23,506
That's impossible!

67
00:06:23,616 --> 00:06:25,015
The comm link's dead!

68
00:06:25,118 --> 00:06:27,951
They left us here.
Don't worry, we're getting home!

69
00:07:09,629 --> 00:07:10,789
Donnie?

70
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:14,627
Donnie!

71
00:08:43,256 --> 00:08:44,689
Come on, boy!

72
00:08:46,459 --> 00:08:47,721
Come on, Sam!

73
00:08:49,529 --> 00:08:51,656
What're you doing, huh?
What're you doing?

74
00:08:51,764 --> 00:08:52,788
Come on.

75
00:08:52,899 --> 00:08:53,991
What? I got nothing.

76
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:55,167
What?

77
00:08:56,269 --> 00:08:58,362
All right, come on, let's go. Let's go.

78
00:09:00,706 --> 00:09:02,105
That's a good boy.

79
00:09:15,288 --> 00:09:16,778
Good boy.

80
00:09:22,528 --> 00:09:25,395
Well, let's see what lies
they're trying to sell us today.

81
00:09:29,335 --> 00:09:30,359
Here, boy.

82
00:09:31,737 --> 00:09:32,999
Good boy.

83
00:09:43,416 --> 00:09:47,045
Gunnery Sergeant Bob Lee Swagger.

84
00:09:47,153 --> 00:09:49,644
USMC, retired.

85
00:09:50,356 --> 00:09:52,119
He is the best there is.

86
00:09:52,224 --> 00:09:54,818
His last assignment went wrong.

87
00:09:54,927 --> 00:09:58,226
Put in unfriendly territory on a loan-out
and left as expendable.

88
00:09:58,331 --> 00:10:01,767
Opposing force sent an attack
helicopter and a hundred-man company.

89
00:10:01,867 --> 00:10:04,700
His best friend and spotter was killed.

90
00:10:04,804 --> 00:10:06,066
No official report.

91
00:10:06,172 --> 00:10:10,404
Ghost report says he inflicted
70 percent casualties, the rest fled.

92
00:10:10,509 --> 00:10:12,602
The agency asset
that left them there to die?

93
00:10:12,712 --> 00:10:15,875
Suddenly removed from
the face of the earth two weeks after.

94
00:10:15,982 --> 00:10:17,882
They never laid it at Bob Lee's feet.

95
00:10:17,984 --> 00:10:19,747
He retired a week later.

96
00:10:19,852 --> 00:10:22,946
I guess Bob Lee didn't think
he was expendable.

97
00:10:33,866 --> 00:10:35,390
Grows and shoots his own food.

98
00:10:35,501 --> 00:10:37,696
Yeah, he rarely ventures out at all.

99
00:10:37,803 --> 00:10:41,933
This is a man
with a history of duty and patriotism.

100
00:10:42,041 --> 00:10:45,738
- Not as punch lines, but as core beliefs.
- Aye.

101
00:10:45,845 --> 00:10:49,246
Some people don't know what to do
when their belief system collapses.

102
00:10:49,949 --> 00:10:51,678
Bob Lee is one of those.

103
00:11:01,827 --> 00:11:03,055
You sure, boy?

104
00:11:16,342 --> 00:11:19,834
Nope. I ain't buying. I don't want any.

105
00:11:19,945 --> 00:11:23,642
You guys turn around and go back
to wherever you came from.

106
00:11:24,517 --> 00:11:26,917
Bob Lee Swagger?

107
00:11:27,019 --> 00:11:29,044
My name is Colonel Isaac Johnson.

108
00:11:29,455 --> 00:11:30,717
You're a hard man to find.

109
00:11:30,823 --> 00:11:32,085
But not hard enough.

110
00:11:32,191 --> 00:11:33,715
Come a long way to see you.

111
00:11:34,060 --> 00:11:36,028
We have some business
needs your attention.

112
00:11:36,128 --> 00:11:37,686
You wanna use your low gear
going down the road

113
00:11:37,797 --> 00:11:38,889
or your brakes'll go.

114
00:11:38,998 --> 00:11:41,865
- Come here. Come here, boy.
- Don't do that.

115
00:11:43,069 --> 00:11:46,368
Come near the porch I didn't invite you,
you'd have to shoot the dog.

116
00:11:47,473 --> 00:11:48,963
That's a slow draw you got there.

117
00:11:49,075 --> 00:11:50,508
Sure you want to do that?

118
00:11:50,943 --> 00:11:52,433
Shoot a dog in this county
on a man's land,

119
00:11:52,545 --> 00:11:54,877
I'd bury you in the hill,
and tell the sheriff a month or two later.

120
00:11:54,980 --> 00:11:56,106
He understands.

121
00:11:57,583 --> 00:11:59,141
Take your hand off your weapon.

122
00:11:59,251 --> 00:12:00,377
Slowly.

123
00:12:00,653 --> 00:12:03,622
So the gunnery sergeant
doesn't have to bury you in the hill.

124
00:12:05,858 --> 00:12:07,587
I don't carry a gun.

125
00:12:11,964 --> 00:12:13,090
You know what that is?

126
00:12:13,199 --> 00:12:15,133
It's a Congressional Medal of Honor.

127
00:12:15,701 --> 00:12:17,225
They don't hand those out easy.

128
00:12:17,403 --> 00:12:18,370
Yours?

129
00:12:18,671 --> 00:12:20,070
Yeah.

130
00:12:20,172 --> 00:12:22,163
Your father had one, didn't he?

131
00:12:22,274 --> 00:12:23,798
What did you do?

132
00:12:23,909 --> 00:12:27,640
Something foolhardy.
Kept some other boys alive.

133
00:12:27,747 --> 00:12:29,510
Will you give me five minutes?

134
00:12:31,984 --> 00:12:33,713
Yeah, your dog stays outside.

135
00:12:34,920 --> 00:12:36,547
Come on, boy. Get in there.

136
00:12:37,957 --> 00:12:42,189
I need you to plan
a presidential assassination.

137
00:12:42,294 --> 00:12:43,318
Whose president?

138
00:12:43,429 --> 00:12:44,453
Ours.

139
00:12:46,132 --> 00:12:47,463
I didn't say "execute".

140
00:12:48,234 --> 00:12:49,201
Plan.

141
00:12:50,002 --> 00:12:52,061
So it can be stopped.

142
00:12:52,171 --> 00:12:55,800
There's gonna be an attempt on the life
of the President in the next two weeks.

143
00:12:55,908 --> 00:12:59,241
Code was broken
on an anonymous transmission.

144
00:13:01,147 --> 00:13:02,910
It was internal.

145
00:13:03,015 --> 00:13:05,381
We can't go to the usual agencies.

146
00:13:05,484 --> 00:13:08,317
The government itself
has been penetrated.

147
00:13:08,420 --> 00:13:13,881
The President has three
public engagements during that time.

148
00:13:13,993 --> 00:13:18,487
Baltimore, Philadelphia,
Washington, D.C.

149
00:13:18,597 --> 00:13:21,430
Standard Secret Service
protective cordon

150
00:13:21,734 --> 00:13:24,362
is out to 880 yards.

151
00:13:24,470 --> 00:13:29,134
But this intercept claims that the shot
will be taken from beyond a mile.

152
00:13:29,241 --> 00:13:32,233
We need you to scout,
tell us how you would do it,

153
00:13:32,611 --> 00:13:34,101
so we could stop it.

154
00:13:35,080 --> 00:13:39,608
I'm not entirely convinced
that a shot like this could be made.

155
00:13:40,920 --> 00:13:43,115
But let's not take the chance.

156
00:13:44,356 --> 00:13:46,551
Your longer shots
were never confirmed.

157
00:13:46,659 --> 00:13:48,559
That's because long shots
generally go places

158
00:13:48,661 --> 00:13:51,494
you wouldn't wanna have
to go afterwards to confirm them.

159
00:13:51,597 --> 00:13:54,191
Confirmation's a desk pogue's problem.

160
00:13:55,034 --> 00:13:57,298
You know what it takes
to make a shot at that range?

161
00:13:57,403 --> 00:13:58,927
Everything comes into play that far.

162
00:13:59,038 --> 00:14:02,132
Humidity, elevation, temperature,
wind, spindrift.

163
00:14:02,241 --> 00:14:03,572
There's a 6- to10-second flight time

164
00:14:03,676 --> 00:14:05,769
so you have to shoot
at where the target's going to be.

165
00:14:05,878 --> 00:14:08,972
Even the Coriolis effect,
the spin of the Earth, comes into play.

166
00:14:09,081 --> 00:14:11,311
President'll be wearing body amour.
That means a headshot,

167
00:14:11,417 --> 00:14:12,577
at over a mile.

168
00:14:12,685 --> 00:14:14,949
You believe there's a shooter involved
capable of making this shot?

169
00:14:15,054 --> 00:14:16,282
Yes.

170
00:14:16,388 --> 00:14:18,754
Well, then you got a real problem.
You need to find the shooter.

171
00:14:18,858 --> 00:14:21,227
That's being worked on
from another direction.

172
00:14:21,427 --> 00:14:23,088
We need you to do this.

173
00:14:23,195 --> 00:14:25,163
Don't really like the President much.

174
00:14:25,264 --> 00:14:27,164
Didn't like the one before
that much, either.

175
00:14:27,266 --> 00:14:29,131
You like the idea of the President?

176
00:14:29,501 --> 00:14:30,968
Living in a free country?

177
00:14:31,070 --> 00:14:33,504
Do we allow America
to be ruled by thugs?

178
00:14:33,606 --> 00:14:35,369
Sure, some years we do.

179
00:14:36,609 --> 00:14:39,476
I believe you stood before a flag

180
00:14:39,979 --> 00:14:41,241
and solemnly swore

181
00:14:42,147 --> 00:14:46,015
that you'd support and defend
the Constitution of the United States

182
00:14:46,118 --> 00:14:47,779
against all enemies,

183
00:14:47,887 --> 00:14:49,514
foreign and domestic.

184
00:14:49,622 --> 00:14:51,556
I think your five minutes is up.

185
00:15:01,033 --> 00:15:02,557
Listen to me, son.

186
00:15:04,637 --> 00:15:06,764
I don't want you to turn on the TV
next week

187
00:15:07,973 --> 00:15:10,271
and see the President dead,

188
00:15:10,376 --> 00:15:13,038
and know you could've done
something about it.

189
00:15:13,879 --> 00:15:15,904
Don't do that to yourself.

190
00:15:36,702 --> 00:15:38,499
Is that the new one?

191
00:15:38,604 --> 00:15:39,866
The truck.

192
00:15:41,373 --> 00:15:42,840
You got the big engine in there?

193
00:15:42,942 --> 00:15:46,503
Wow, look at that, huh? Eight-liter V8.

194
00:15:46,612 --> 00:15:50,309
Thing's so big, EPA doesn't even bother
to give you the gas mileage for it.

195
00:15:50,416 --> 00:15:51,974
You mind if I take a picture?

196
00:15:53,786 --> 00:15:55,310
This is beautiful.

197
00:15:59,825 --> 00:16:02,555
Someone will be at this number
night or day.

198
00:16:07,733 --> 00:16:10,361
You see what he did?
He didn't need a photo of the engine.

199
00:16:10,469 --> 00:16:12,767
No, he doesn't give a rat's ass
about the engine.

200
00:16:12,871 --> 00:16:14,395
He's trained in counterintel.

201
00:16:14,506 --> 00:16:16,838
Backed up far enough
to take a picture of the plates.

202
00:16:16,942 --> 00:16:18,432
This is our guy.

203
00:16:18,544 --> 00:16:19,943
I thought he turned you down.

204
00:16:20,045 --> 00:16:22,479
He said yes. He just doesn't know it yet.

205
00:17:37,289 --> 00:17:39,416
1,760's a mile.

206
00:17:40,292 --> 00:17:43,887
It's a far piece, Sam.
Think the President ought to worry?

207
00:18:15,727 --> 00:18:17,319
Yeah, I think he better worry.

208
00:18:32,077 --> 00:18:33,806
Yeah, he'll be fine.

209
00:18:34,980 --> 00:18:38,939
Just feed him once a day. Read him
a few ballistics tables if he looks lonely.

210
00:18:39,051 --> 00:18:40,313
Yep. I'm out.

211
00:18:42,121 --> 00:18:43,554
Come here, buddy.

212
00:18:44,323 --> 00:18:45,483
Okay.

213
00:18:46,191 --> 00:18:49,649
Think you'll be able to tough it out
without me for a couple days?

214
00:18:50,496 --> 00:18:51,463
Yeah.

215
00:20:18,650 --> 00:20:20,777
This is Command Post.
What's your status? Over.

216
00:20:20,886 --> 00:20:22,717
Yeah, we're finishing up here on 6th.

217
00:20:22,821 --> 00:20:25,619
Roger that. We copy.
Checkpoint down, over.

218
00:20:38,604 --> 00:20:43,371
Before you stands Independence Hall,
the birthplace of the United States

219
00:20:43,475 --> 00:20:46,376
and one of the most important buildings
in American history.

220
00:20:46,778 --> 00:20:48,609
Built in 1732...

221
00:20:48,714 --> 00:20:50,841
Keep a visual eye on 72nd...

222
00:20:50,949 --> 00:20:53,247
...both the Declaration of Independence
and the U.S. Constitution

223
00:20:53,352 --> 00:20:55,513
were debated and signed here.

224
00:21:04,096 --> 00:21:05,085
Out of the three cities,

225
00:21:05,197 --> 00:21:08,132
there's only one with
a reasonably high chance of success.

226
00:21:08,800 --> 00:21:10,028
There was no room in Baltimore.

227
00:21:10,135 --> 00:21:11,568
Street isn't wide enough to correct
for the windage,

228
00:21:11,670 --> 00:21:13,433
buildings are in the way.

229
00:21:13,538 --> 00:21:15,062
D.C.'s a pure suicide mission.

230
00:21:15,173 --> 00:21:17,299
I mean, unless you're sure
your shooter's interested in 70 virgins

231
00:21:17,409 --> 00:21:18,433
waiting for him in the afterlife,

232
00:21:18,543 --> 00:21:20,067
I'd rule that out.

233
00:21:20,178 --> 00:21:21,304
Shot's got to be taken from Philly.

234
00:21:22,114 --> 00:21:24,014
From beyond 1,800 yards, though.

235
00:21:24,116 --> 00:21:25,583
It's one of six possible locations,

236
00:21:25,684 --> 00:21:28,619
approximately five stories
above the President's location.

237
00:21:29,221 --> 00:21:31,849
Flight time of the bullet that distance
is five to six seconds.

238
00:21:31,957 --> 00:21:33,185
They'll have to wait
till he takes the podium,

239
00:21:33,292 --> 00:21:34,816
several lines into his speech.

240
00:21:34,926 --> 00:21:37,724
That way he'd be completely static,
obviously at his most exposed.

241
00:21:37,829 --> 00:21:39,763
Shot requires a large-caliber weapon.

242
00:21:39,865 --> 00:21:42,629
Expect the bullet to be handmade,
bronzed alloy turned on a lathe.

243
00:21:42,734 --> 00:21:44,031
Slightly lower ballistics coefficient,

244
00:21:44,136 --> 00:21:45,160
touch more slippery.

245
00:21:45,270 --> 00:21:46,760
Least that's what I'd do.

246
00:21:46,872 --> 00:21:49,204
You can kill him from that far away?

247
00:21:51,209 --> 00:21:53,177
Mile and a half, the bullet's
going to strike with more energy

248
00:21:53,278 --> 00:21:54,472
than a .44 Magnum point blank.

249
00:21:54,579 --> 00:21:56,274
Yeah, I think you can kill him.

250
00:21:56,882 --> 00:21:58,144
The challenge is the wind.

251
00:21:58,250 --> 00:22:00,115
Lightest breeze uncorrected
at that distance

252
00:22:00,218 --> 00:22:01,515
is enough to ruin the shot.

253
00:22:01,620 --> 00:22:04,817
He's gonna need indicators between
the podium and the shooting position.

254
00:22:04,923 --> 00:22:06,413
Velocity corrections are easy,

255
00:22:06,525 --> 00:22:08,322
