for hundreds of years.

505
00:43:17,194 --> 00:43:19,424
It has something to do
with osmotic pressure.

506
00:43:19,530 --> 00:43:21,964
It was popular
during the Napoleonic War.

507
00:43:22,066 --> 00:43:24,534
You go into Howard's office
with the Napoleonic War,

508
00:43:24,635 --> 00:43:25,829
he's gonna put you on psych leave.

509
00:43:25,936 --> 00:43:28,166
Go back to your desk.
I'm saving your life.

510
00:43:50,127 --> 00:43:51,094
One thing is...

511
00:43:57,434 --> 00:43:59,061
...1790 to 1800.

512
00:44:00,404 --> 00:44:01,371
One thing is...

513
00:45:17,781 --> 00:45:18,975
I'm sorry to bother you, ma'am.

514
00:45:19,083 --> 00:45:20,516
I know who you are.

515
00:45:20,617 --> 00:45:23,484
You're Bob Lee. Swagger.
Donnie's old partner.

516
00:45:23,587 --> 00:45:26,215
Look, I didn't shoot the President.

517
00:45:26,323 --> 00:45:27,415
I know.

518
00:45:27,524 --> 00:45:28,513
You do?

519
00:45:28,625 --> 00:45:32,152
The President's not dead.
Ethiopian Archbishop is.

520
00:45:34,198 --> 00:45:36,758
Why in the hell
would somebody want to shoot him?

521
00:45:37,501 --> 00:45:38,627
Look, you're a nurse, right?

522
00:45:38,736 --> 00:45:43,332
No. No, that was Donnie's dream.
I couldn't stand the blood.

523
00:45:43,440 --> 00:45:44,634
I teach the third grade.

524
00:45:45,342 --> 00:45:46,934
- Please.
- Look, you should go.

525
00:45:47,044 --> 00:45:48,136
Please.

526
00:45:48,345 --> 00:45:49,403
Please?

527
00:45:49,747 --> 00:45:51,738
I didn't do whatever they said I did.

528
00:45:52,349 --> 00:45:53,316
I swear.

529
00:45:53,817 --> 00:45:56,047
I'm in some bad trouble
and I need some help.

530
00:45:56,153 --> 00:45:58,678
I wouldn't have come all the way here
to lie to you.

531
00:46:02,159 --> 00:46:04,855
You still figuring on shooting me?

532
00:46:04,962 --> 00:46:07,760
Only that shotgun's a little long
to bring up fast.

533
00:46:07,865 --> 00:46:10,993
Look, if you're going to do it,
just get it over with.

534
00:46:11,101 --> 00:46:13,069
I ain't got nowhere else to go.

535
00:46:16,306 --> 00:46:20,037
Pull the truck in the garage.
The neighbors'll be up in a minute.

536
00:46:20,144 --> 00:46:21,668
You'd best call me Sarah.

537
00:46:21,779 --> 00:46:22,973
All right.

538
00:46:38,295 --> 00:46:40,456
911, what's your emergency?

539
00:47:09,159 --> 00:47:10,183
Hello?

540
00:47:10,294 --> 00:47:12,125
This is 911. We received a hang-up
from this location.

541
00:47:12,229 --> 00:47:14,754
Yeah, neighbor's dog knocked over
the trash cans

542
00:47:14,865 --> 00:47:17,356
and scared the hell out of me.
Everything's fine. Thanks.

543
00:47:17,467 --> 00:47:18,434
Okay, then.

544
00:47:24,541 --> 00:47:27,704
Seems you call the police and hang up
without saying anything,

545
00:47:27,811 --> 00:47:29,870
they call you back right away.

546
00:47:36,119 --> 00:47:38,485
I should've come
and seen you in person.

547
00:47:41,558 --> 00:47:43,890
Before. I mean, then.

548
00:47:43,994 --> 00:47:45,359
Yeah, I read the letter.

549
00:47:47,431 --> 00:47:48,728
It was okay.

550
00:47:50,801 --> 00:47:52,996
And once a year I got the flowers.

551
00:47:55,539 --> 00:47:57,029
You don't look real good.

552
00:47:58,475 --> 00:48:02,343
I'm supposed to be dead.
Been a long night.

553
00:48:02,446 --> 00:48:04,414
Why aren't you?

554
00:48:04,514 --> 00:48:06,880
Well, the U.S. government spent
a lot of time and money

555
00:48:06,984 --> 00:48:08,781
teaching me how not to die

556
00:48:08,886 --> 00:48:11,377
after they got done teaching me
how to kill people.

557
00:48:12,756 --> 00:48:15,088
So how is it I'm supposed to help you?

558
00:48:16,360 --> 00:48:20,558
You can do a running cross-stitch,
finish it with an embroidery knot?

559
00:48:20,664 --> 00:48:21,631
Yeah.

560
00:48:31,575 --> 00:48:33,566
You got to try to spread it out.

561
00:48:33,677 --> 00:48:36,043
It's gonna look odd
you buy it all in one place.

562
00:48:44,153 --> 00:48:46,986
How can it be three years ago
when it seems like ten?

563
00:48:50,893 --> 00:48:52,520
Mileage can be rough.

564
00:49:03,906 --> 00:49:05,669
No one ever beats me in.

565
00:49:13,048 --> 00:49:14,310
You never left.

566
00:49:15,217 --> 00:49:17,344
Everyone keeps telling me I'm crazy.

567
00:49:17,453 --> 00:49:20,581
Like I didn't see what I saw,
or heard what I heard.

568
00:49:21,657 --> 00:49:24,125
I'm not crazy, though.
You think I'm crazy?

569
00:49:25,494 --> 00:49:27,621
Where did all this stuff come from?

570
00:49:28,364 --> 00:49:31,424
At first I thought
it was Washington, Quantico.

571
00:49:31,534 --> 00:49:35,436
I checked and it didn't.
It just magically arrived.

572
00:49:35,538 --> 00:49:39,941
Cooperating agencies, ATF, NRO,
places that don't even have initials

573
00:49:40,042 --> 00:49:42,840
they cooperate
in times of national emergency.

574
00:49:43,445 --> 00:49:44,571
You need to get some sleep.

575
00:49:44,680 --> 00:49:47,444
You know that the first
ballistics diagram got here

576
00:49:47,550 --> 00:49:49,381
22 minutes after the shooting.

577
00:49:49,485 --> 00:49:50,509
We're good at our jobs.

578
00:49:50,619 --> 00:49:53,087
12 minutes after the shooting,
they were still scrambling choppers.

579
00:49:53,189 --> 00:49:54,315
The scene was locked down.

580
00:49:55,658 --> 00:49:58,923
How did they get a reverse azimuth
10 minutes after that?

581
00:49:59,028 --> 00:50:00,120
I mean, we work
for the federal government.

582
00:50:00,229 --> 00:50:01,560
We're not that good at our jobs.

583
00:50:02,431 --> 00:50:04,023
- You want to see something?
- Probably not.

584
00:50:04,133 --> 00:50:05,498
I downloaded this.

585
00:50:05,601 --> 00:50:06,727
This is a full-scale printout

586
00:50:06,835 --> 00:50:09,827
of a target Swagger shot
two years ago at 1,000 yards.

587
00:50:09,939 --> 00:50:13,204
I punched in the holes myself.
It was at a competition.

588
00:50:13,309 --> 00:50:18,042
I read an article. It said Swagger shot
a silver dollar at a grand.

589
00:50:18,147 --> 00:50:19,341
Five shots,

590
00:50:19,682 --> 00:50:20,910
at 1,000 yards,

591
00:50:21,150 --> 00:50:23,414
an inch-and-a-half spread.
An inch and a half!

592
00:50:25,788 --> 00:50:27,278
It was the capital of the United States...

593
00:50:27,389 --> 00:50:30,916
That's the flag behind the President.
It's barely waving.

594
00:50:31,026 --> 00:50:32,459
This is the wind speed and direction

595
00:50:32,561 --> 00:50:33,823
according to the
National Weather Service

596
00:50:33,929 --> 00:50:36,227
at the time of the shot. I did the math.

597
00:50:36,332 --> 00:50:38,960
Now, how does a man who can do that

598
00:50:39,802 --> 00:50:43,033
miss by two-and-a-half feet
at 2,000 yards?

599
00:50:43,706 --> 00:50:44,832
I don't get it.

600
00:50:44,940 --> 00:50:47,773
You've had a long night.
Let it go and get some sleep.

601
00:50:47,876 --> 00:50:50,003
You know, I saw Timmons interviewed.

602
00:50:50,112 --> 00:50:52,342
He said he was walking foot patrol,

603
00:50:52,448 --> 00:50:55,042
saw a rifle barrel
sticking out of a window,

604
00:50:55,150 --> 00:50:57,983
went upstairs to investigate,
and shot Swagger.

605
00:50:58,087 --> 00:50:59,987
No sniper sticks his rifle
out of a window.

606
00:51:00,089 --> 00:51:02,853
They shoot from cover,
back in the room.

607
00:51:03,225 --> 00:51:05,159
It doesn't make any sense.

608
00:51:07,396 --> 00:51:09,057
- I'm gonna talk to Timmons.
- No, you're not.

609
00:51:09,164 --> 00:51:11,257
Why? 'Cause they're gonna fire me
if I do?

610
00:51:12,167 --> 00:51:14,863
Timmons was killed by a mugger
in an alley last night.

611
00:51:18,974 --> 00:51:21,033
In a conspiracy,
all loose ends are trimmed.

612
00:51:21,677 --> 00:51:23,542
Jack Ruby shoots Oswald?

613
00:51:23,646 --> 00:51:25,637
Bad things happen to good people.

614
00:51:25,748 --> 00:51:26,772
Yeah, not that quick, they don't.

615
00:51:32,821 --> 00:51:35,221
Well, I stopped the bleeding
temporarily.

616
00:51:36,158 --> 00:51:38,388
But it'll cut loose again.

617
00:51:38,494 --> 00:51:41,793
I held off the worst of the infection,
but you're gonna have to open it up,

618
00:51:41,897 --> 00:51:44,695
cut out and scrub away
anything that's dead,

619
00:51:44,800 --> 00:51:47,667
working your way out,
sewing it together

620
00:51:47,770 --> 00:51:50,568
and you got to try to make sure
you don't re-infect it.

621
00:51:53,008 --> 00:51:54,441
You ready for this?

622
00:51:56,779 --> 00:51:59,475
I'm going to do all those Whip-It!'s
and pass out.

623
00:52:02,651 --> 00:52:03,982
Good luck, okay?

624
00:53:17,960 --> 00:53:21,361
I need you to plan
a presidential assassination.

625
00:53:21,463 --> 00:53:22,896
That our guy in the collar?

626
00:53:22,998 --> 00:53:24,226
Whose president?

627
00:53:24,333 --> 00:53:25,732
I didn't say "execute".

628
00:53:25,834 --> 00:53:28,735
He's getting a medal. Know it?

629
00:53:28,837 --> 00:53:31,067
The Archbishop of Ethiopia.

630
00:53:35,477 --> 00:53:36,967
You need to find the shooter.

631
00:53:40,315 --> 00:53:41,282
No.

632
00:55:34,630 --> 00:55:37,258
Two-and-a-half days, shot twice,
no sign?

633
00:55:37,366 --> 00:55:38,765
Find me something.

634
00:55:38,867 --> 00:55:41,028
Maybe he crawled into a hole and died.

635
00:55:42,237 --> 00:55:43,898
He's not dead.

636
00:55:45,741 --> 00:55:47,140
Tear apart his life.

637
00:55:47,242 --> 00:55:48,573
Again.

638
00:55:53,782 --> 00:55:54,840
Go okay?

639
00:56:00,188 --> 00:56:01,553
I've been hallucinating.

640
00:56:04,560 --> 00:56:06,494
Something I need to tell you.

641
00:56:09,731 --> 00:56:11,562
Ralphie's dead.

642
00:56:11,667 --> 00:56:12,895
Who's Ralphie?

643
00:56:14,002 --> 00:56:15,469
Well, they said you shot your dog

644
00:56:15,571 --> 00:56:17,471
'cause you knew
you weren't coming back.

645
00:56:17,573 --> 00:56:19,040
They said that, huh?

646
00:56:23,445 --> 00:56:24,878
Name was Sam.

647
00:56:25,981 --> 00:56:28,449
He was a good dog.
I raised him from a pup.

648
00:56:32,521 --> 00:56:33,715
You okay?

649
00:56:35,691 --> 00:56:36,658
No.

650
00:56:37,826 --> 00:56:39,521
What are you gonna do?

651
00:56:40,996 --> 00:56:42,657
I'll get better.

652
00:56:44,533 --> 00:56:47,024
Then I'm going to burn
their playhouse down.

653
00:57:22,904 --> 00:57:23,996
Can I help you?

654
00:57:53,001 --> 00:57:54,127
Hold still.

655
00:58:05,747 --> 00:58:07,612
I been meaning to ask you.

656
00:58:08,350 --> 00:58:10,011
You have a boyfriend?

657
00:58:12,054 --> 00:58:13,078
Why?

658
00:58:14,289 --> 00:58:16,883
Am I still supposed to be
the grieving widow?

659
00:58:16,992 --> 00:58:18,653
It's been three years.

660
00:58:18,760 --> 00:58:19,727
No.

661
00:58:20,295 --> 00:58:21,728
Just wonder if I'm gonna have
to shoot somebody

662
00:58:21,830 --> 00:58:22,990
walks through that door
without knocking,

663
00:58:23,098 --> 00:58:25,032
wondering where you've been.

664
00:58:27,302 --> 00:58:28,894
Well, no.

665
00:58:29,004 --> 00:58:31,234
Nothing steady. No boyfriend.

666
00:58:55,731 --> 00:58:57,028
Not bad.

667
00:58:58,300 --> 00:58:59,961
A little stiff, but...

668
00:59:01,770 --> 00:59:02,737
Hey.

669
00:59:03,972 --> 00:59:06,668
You know, you would've made
one hell of a nurse.

670
00:59:07,909 --> 00:59:09,774
That was really brave, what you did.

671
00:59:10,145 --> 00:59:11,305
You saved my life.

672
00:59:15,446 --> 00:59:18,108
I'm better. I better get to it.

673
00:59:18,216 --> 00:59:20,548
They're never gonna stop chasing you.

674
00:59:21,652 --> 00:59:22,744
Never.

675
00:59:24,021 --> 00:59:26,182
They're never gonna stop looking.

676
00:59:28,059 --> 00:59:31,324
In the meantime,
they need someone else to find.

677
00:59:31,429 --> 00:59:32,919
I'm going to give them him.

678
00:59:33,030 --> 00:59:34,497
Excuse me?

679
00:59:35,666 --> 00:59:38,760
May be a way to get two birds
with that stone, too.

680
00:59:47,278 --> 00:59:49,143
- Swagger?
- Hey.

681
00:59:58,956 --> 01:00:01,686
The gun Donnie learned to hunt with
when he was a kid.

682
01:00:03,427 --> 01:00:06,863
It ain't much, but it shoots true.

683
01:00:06,964 --> 01:00:09,398
I cleaned and oiled it
before I put it away.

684
01:00:09,500 --> 01:00:10,558
You sure?

685
01:00:11,802 --> 01:00:12,769
Yeah.

686
01:00:17,108 --> 01:00:18,473
Why'd you go?

687
01:00:19,243 --> 01:00:21,006
When they came to see you.

688
01:00:23,414 --> 01:00:25,575
They know which buttons to press.

689
01:00:26,417 --> 01:00:28,476
I'm still enough of a sucker,
you press that patriot button,

690
01:00:28,586 --> 01:00:32,181
I'll sit up in my chair and say,
"Which way you want me to go, boss?"

691
01:00:32,290 --> 01:00:35,919
I mean, I ain't real proud of it,
but I ain't ashamed, either.

692
01:00:37,295 --> 01:00:38,660
You know, I got a plan,

693
01:00:40,097 --> 01:00:42,361
but I think I'm going to need your help.

694
01:00:42,533 --> 01:00:44,467
Okay. I'll do it.

695
01:00:45,169 --> 01:00:47,501
I haven't even told you what it is yet.

696
01:00:48,072 --> 01:00:49,198
I know.

697
01:00:57,081 --> 01:00:58,173
Look.

698
01:00:59,250 --> 01:01:00,484
It was my fault.

699
01:01:03,287 --> 01:01:04,254
What?

700
01:01:07,825 --> 01:01:09,986
You know, with Donnie.
I should never have...

701
01:01:17,068 --> 01:01:18,057
What?

702
01:01:23,240 --> 01:01:24,867
Don't you dare.

703
01:01:26,911 --> 01:01:29,971
Don't you try and take that
away from him.

704
01:01:31,015 --> 01:01:34,746
He knew exactly what he was doing
when he enlisted.

705
01:01:34,852 --> 01:01:35,944
He knew exactly what he was doing

706
01:01:36,053 --> 01:01:38,817
when he enrolled
in scout sniper training.

707
01:01:40,558 --> 01:01:42,492
He loved what he did.

708
01:01:42,593 --> 01:01:44,561
No one made him do it.

709
01:01:46,998 --> 01:01:49,125
That ain't yours to carry.

710
01:01:52,470 --> 01:01:53,664
You're right.

711
01:01:55,272 --> 01:01:56,705
I'm sorry I tried.

712
01:02:22,600 --> 01:02:23,862
It's okay.

713
01:02:29,874 --> 01:02:32,138
I need you to meet with this FBI agent.

714
01:02:32,243 --> 01:02:35,007
Use him to flush Johnson
out of his hiding place.

715
01:02:35,112 --> 01:02:39,105
Give him the vehicle ID number.
He'll do what he's trained to do.

716
01:02:39,216 --> 01:02:41,684
You get in and get out.
Don't get caught.

717
01:02:41,986 --> 01:02:43,578
You get caught, I get caught.

718
01:02:43,687 --> 01:02:45,245
You know what that is?

719
01:02:47,024 --> 01:02:49,754
Says he didn't shoot no one,
but I don't know.

720
01:02:49,860 --> 01:02:51,157
Well, he's been staying with me.

721
01:02:51,262 --> 01:02:53,321
Who's been staying with you?
Bob Lee Swagger?

722
01:03:02,039 --> 01:03:06,032
The plates are probably fake.
Pretty sure the other number's real.

723
01:03:06,143 --> 01:03:07,735
- And what is this?
- A VIN number.

724
01:03:07,845 --> 01:03:11,076
Seems no one goes through
the trouble to change them anymore.

725
01:03:12,316 --> 01:03:15,217
And you're going to sit real still
until I'm long gone.

726
01:03:46,851 --> 01:03:48,045
See the guy in the Eagles jacket?

727
01:04:13,744 --> 01:04:15,644
Excuse me, sir.
Can I see some ID, please?

728
01:04:22,887 --> 01:04:25,219
Sir, I'm going to need you
to take off your hat

729
01:04:25,322 --> 01:04:26,482
and show me some ID.

730
01:04:30,594 --> 01:04:32,186
I'm not gonna ask you again.

731
01:04:33,597 --> 01:04:35,360
Take your hat off, asshole!

732
01:04:44,475 --> 01:04:47,308
Get on the ground!
Get your ass on the ground!

733
01:05:20,644 --> 01:05:21,872
Hey, how's it going?

734
01:05:23,681 --> 01:05:24,875
Hey, John.

735
01:05:48,405 --> 01:05:49,599
- Hey, Ed?
- Yeah.

736
01:05:49,707 --> 01:05:51,641
You got that Stevens file
we wanted back?

737
01:05:54,111 --> 01:05:57,274
How badly do you want to know?
Because this will get you fired.

738
01:05:57,615 --> 01:06:03,315
Well, I have to go before
the Office of Professional Responsibility

739
01:06:03,420 --> 01:06:05,411
in 45 minutes for a review.

740
01:06:05,522 --> 01:06:08,548
I'm gonna get fired anyway.
I'm done worrying about that.

741
01:06:09,760 --> 01:06:11,728
What do you think?

742
01:06:12,429 --> 01:06:14,863
I think that CNN got the tapes
before we did,

743
01:06:14,965 --> 01:06:17,297
already edited together
to show the angles.

744
01:06:17,401 --> 01:06:18,493
Who delivered them?

745
01:06:18,602 --> 01:06:22,003
An unnamed agency
who will never confirm or deny.

746
01:06:22,106 --> 01:06:24,074
They denied, which is a...

747
01:06:26,677 --> 01:06:29,840
Which is a confirmation of sorts.

748
01:06:29,947 --> 01:06:31,778
Of what?

749
01:06:31,882 --> 01:06:35,409
That you are asking questions
way outside your pay grade.

750
01:06:35,519 --> 01:06:36,645
Oh, come on, just tell me.

751
01:06:36,754 --> 01:06:38,244
You don't want to be here
for that review.

752
01:06:38,355 --> 01:06:41,916
They don't have to stop at firing you.
They can charge you and hold you.

753
01:06:50,768 --> 01:06:54,499
The ASAC's job
comes with Delta clearance.

754
01:06:57,541 --> 01:06:58,838
- Thank you.
- Go.

755
01:07:06,016 --> 01:07:08,007
This is a copy of a chat room transcript.

756
01:07:08,118 --> 01:07:11,212
These guys talk about everything.
I didn't give it much thought at the time.

757
01:07:11,322 --> 01:07:13,790
We just traced it to a donut shop
with free WiFi.

758
01:07:13,891 --> 01:07:16,655
But this,
this is a Delta-level clearance request

759
01:07:16,760 --> 01:07:19,558
out of the FBI field office in Philadelphia
seven minutes ago.

760
01:07:19,663 --> 01:07:22,257
Funny thing,
Google Maps puts the donut shop

761
01:07:22,366 --> 01:07:24,891
only three blocks away
from the field office.

762
01:07:25,002 --> 01:07:28,062
There's only one guy who met
with Swagger before he disappeared.

763
01:07:28,172 --> 01:07:29,366
He lives in Philly.

764
01:07:29,606 --> 01:07:31,039
And he works for the FBI.

765
01:07:32,343 --> 01:07:33,674
Nicholas Memphis.

766
01:07:34,111 --> 01:07:37,569
...really strange company.
Contracts with a lot of the Fortune 500.

767
01:07:37,681 --> 01:07:40,514
Offices in Virginia, Delaware,
registered in Panama.

768
01:07:40,617 --> 01:07:42,414
They own a boat
that's flagged out of Libya.

769
01:07:42,519 --> 01:07:43,508
They're definitely not government,

770
01:07:43,620 --> 01:07:46,350
but they have high ex-military contacts
like you wouldn't believe.

771
01:07:46,457 --> 01:07:47,651
These are contractors.

772
01:07:47,758 --> 01:07:50,249
I can't tell
what this company does, but...

773
01:07:52,129 --> 01:07:53,118
Hey.

774
01:07:53,230 --> 01:07:54,197
Hey, hey, hey!

775
01:07:59,203 --> 01:08:00,363
Memphis?

776
01:08:00,471 --> 01:08:01,438
Memphis!

777
01:08:08,679 --> 01:08:10,544
For a man who didn't know much,

778
01:08:10,647 --> 01:08:13,946
you sure took a long,
painful time to tell it.

779
01:08:14,051 --> 01:08:15,643
Get him some water.

780
01:08:24,795 --> 01:08:25,853
Good.

781
01:08:36,407 --> 01:08:37,635
Got to pee yet?

782
01:08:37,741 --> 01:08:39,606
Got to flush them drugs
out of your system.

783
01:08:39,710 --> 01:08:42,008
Look awful suspicious
if you were to go and shoot yourself

784
01:08:42,112 --> 01:08:44,376
pumped full of the same shit
the agency uses.

785
01:08:44,481 --> 01:08:46,415
I'm not going to shoot myself.

786
01:08:47,251 --> 01:08:48,343
Sure you will.

787
01:08:49,386 --> 01:08:50,819
Take him out. Get him ready.

788
01:08:50,921 --> 01:08:51,888
No!

789
01:08:57,628 --> 01:08:58,754
That's my gun.

790
01:08:58,862 --> 01:08:59,886
Yeah.

791
01:09:00,431 --> 01:09:02,865
You wrote a real touching
suicide note, too.

792
01:09:02,966 --> 01:09:05,298
All overwrought with guilt
about your mistakes.

793
01:09:12,376 --> 01:09:13,900
Quit your struggling.

794
01:09:17,514 --> 01:09:21,314
This thing works.
It's not the first time we've used it.

795
01:09:25,823 --> 01:09:27,518
Russo. Russo!

796
01:09:27,624 --> 01:09:29,251
Davis, get out here!

797
01:09:34,097 --> 01:09:36,224
What is the goddamn hold-up?

798
01:10:13,804 --> 01:10:17,035
Don't kill me, please!
Don't kill me! I believe you!

799
01:10:17,140 --> 01:10:18,232
Kill you?

800
01:10:18,342 --> 01:10:20,970
Had enough chances.
I wanted you dead, you'd be dead.

801
01:10:22,212 --> 01:10:25,010
What kind of asshole'd
think up a thing like this?

802
01:10:33,257 --> 01:10:36,488
Not bad with a poodle shooter
and a makeshift silencer, huh?

803
01:10:37,794 --> 01:10:39,921
Help me toss these boys in the water?

804
01:10:40,030 --> 01:10:42,328
You set me up and you used me as bait!

805
01:10:42,432 --> 01:10:45,265
You think? Flushed them out, didn't it?

806
01:10:45,369 --> 01:10:46,393
I was kind of hoping to keep one alive,

807
01:10:46,503 --> 01:10:48,596
but they were
kind of determined to kill you.

808
01:10:48,705 --> 01:10:50,935
You can hire a good lawyer,
and I'll call the Bureau.

809
01:10:51,041 --> 01:10:52,975
They can work out some kind of deal.

810
01:10:53,944 --> 01:10:56,811
This is explainable. You can prove
that you didn't shoot the Archbishop.

811
01:10:56,914 --> 01:10:58,040
I don't think you understand.

812
01:10:58,148 --> 01:10:59,342
These boys killed my dog.

813
01:11:02,252 --> 01:11:05,187
Hey, this is the 21st century.
You can't go to war with these people.

814
01:11:05,289 --> 01:11:06,847
In the end, the law is all...

815
01:11:06,957 --> 01:11:09,653
In the end,
the law'll never catch and hold them.

816
01:11:09,760 --> 01:11:11,057
In a year or two,
they'll be back in business.

817
01:11:11,161 --> 01:11:13,686
New names, new messenger boys,
same old story.

818
01:11:13,931 --> 01:11:15,091
And I'll be dead.

819
01:11:15,198 --> 01:11:17,132
It's gonna be
some hard, hairy work, Pork.

820
01:11:17,234 --> 01:11:19,327
There's gonna be more shooting,
and more people are gonna die.

821
01:11:19,436 --> 01:11:22,667
Now, I didn't start it, but be sure as hell
I mean to see it through.

822
01:11:22,773 --> 01:11:25,264
So you get it straight. You in or you out?

823
01:11:28,545 --> 01:11:29,910
You know, I missed a meeting today

824
01:11:30,013 --> 01:11:33,471
where I was going to get fired
for unprofessional conduct

825
01:11:33,584 --> 01:11:36,576
because I was kidnapped by people
that don't exist.

826
01:11:41,224 --> 01:11:42,623
I'll take his legs.

827
01:11:42,726 --> 01:11:44,387
It's a good call, Pork.

828
01:11:44,962 --> 01:11:47,760
You're trying to tell me
a rookie FBI agent

829
01:11:47,864 --> 01:11:49,661
overpowered and killed
the three of them?

830
01:11:49,766 --> 01:11:50,733
No.

831
01:11:51,468 --> 01:11:55,370
They were shot from a distance
of about 200 yards.

832
01:11:57,240 --> 01:11:58,502
With a .22.

833
01:12:00,477 --> 01:12:02,707
- Swagger's alive.
- Yes.

834
01:12:02,813 --> 01:12:04,246
And that young kid,

835
01:12:04,548 --> 01:12:06,072
FBI Agent

836
01:12:08,552 --> 01:12:09,746
Nick Memphis,

837
01:12:09,853 --> 01:12:13,653
who managed to pry out
a Delta-level clearance,

838
01:12:13,757 --> 01:12:17,488
hasn't come back to the office
and is out there with him.

839
01:12:19,663 --> 01:12:20,630
What?

840
01:12:20,731 --> 01:12:22,892
I just went over
Swagger's financials again.

841
01:12:23,367 --> 01:12:27,030
Once a year, he sent flowers
to someone with his Visa card.

842
01:12:27,237 --> 01:12:29,637
I cracked the FTD database,
got an address.

843
01:12:29,740 --> 01:12:32,903
Donnie Fenn's widow.
Anniversary of his death.

844
01:12:33,010 --> 01:12:34,204
She went back to using
her maiden name,

845
01:12:34,311 --> 01:12:36,541
which is why we missed it the first time.

846
01:12:37,714 --> 01:12:39,477
She's maybe the only person
in the entire world

847
01:12:39,583 --> 01:12:41,642
that would believe anything
that Swagger had to say.

848
01:12:41,752 --> 01:12:45,153
Look. Keene City, Kentucky.

849
01:12:45,255 --> 01:12:46,916
It's just within driving range.

850
01:12:47,891 --> 01:12:50,587
- What are you waiting for? Take the jet.
- All right.

851
01:12:58,368 --> 01:13:00,063
We've given Swagger a new war,

852
01:13:00,504 --> 01:13:01,971
he's found a new spotter.

853
01:13:03,340 --> 01:13:04,967
This is about to get worse.

854
01:13:34,071 --> 01:13:35,698
I think we're here.

855
01:13:36,840 --> 01:13:38,068
Hey. Swagger.

856
01:13:42,479 --> 01:13:43,912
I think we're here.

857
01:13:47,017 --> 01:13:49,144
Welcome to Tennessee.

858
01:13:49,252 --> 01:13:51,379
Patron state of shooting stuff.

859
01:13:53,657 --> 01:13:55,090
Hey, who is this guy?

860
01:13:55,192 --> 01:13:58,719
This guy was the greatest gunsmith
east of the Mississippi. He's a legend.

861
01:13:58,829 --> 01:14:00,888
He knows more about guns
and the people who shoot them

862
01:14:00,997 --> 01:14:02,055
than Smith And Wesson.

863
01:14:02,165 --> 01:14:04,656
Don't really matter anymore. He knew
we were coming the last three miles.

864
01:14:04,768 --> 01:14:05,928
- You mind your manners.
- All right.

865
01:14:06,036 --> 01:14:09,631
You boys come a long way.
What you looking for?

866
01:14:09,940 --> 01:14:11,032
Wisdom.

867
01:14:13,076 --> 01:14:14,703
You come to the wrong place.

868
01:14:14,811 --> 01:14:16,073
Maybe.

869
01:14:16,179 --> 01:14:17,771
Say a man wanted to fire a bullet
from one rifle

870
01:14:17,881 --> 01:14:19,542
and have it match exactly to another.

871
01:14:19,649 --> 01:14:21,014
Could that be done?

872
01:14:21,118 --> 01:14:22,142
Take a seat.

873
01:14:23,019 --> 01:14:24,247
Have a chair, son.

874
01:14:28,525 --> 01:14:32,484
If you could get a bullet that had been
shot clean through the first rifle,

875
01:14:32,596 --> 01:14:34,086
could make the grooves match.

876
01:14:34,197 --> 01:14:36,529
Kind of thing ain't been done
in a long time, though.

877
01:14:36,633 --> 01:14:38,157
The bullet that was taken
out of the Archbishop

878
01:14:38,268 --> 01:14:39,826
was completely mangled on impact.

879
01:14:39,936 --> 01:14:42,166
FBI match was metallurgical.

880
01:14:42,272 --> 01:14:43,432
Thank you, Mother.

881
01:14:43,540 --> 01:14:45,940
Yeah, but you couldn't guarantee that
going in, so they had to be sure.

882
01:14:46,042 --> 01:14:48,533
And I still can't figure out
how they could be.

883
01:14:51,481 --> 01:14:53,039
- Good coffee?
- Yep.

884
01:14:55,051 --> 01:14:58,214
Look on your left, there.
Second shelf down.

885
01:14:59,122 --> 01:15:01,317
Red leather spine.

886
01:15:01,525 --> 01:15:04,392
Written by a guy named Schofeld.

887
01:15:05,629 --> 01:15:09,463
Put it there 15 years ago.
Don't figure it's moved since then.

888
01:15:29,152 --> 01:15:31,382
Yeah. Paper patching.

889
01:15:31,488 --> 01:15:34,651
State of the art. 1870s Africa.

890
01:15:34,758 --> 01:15:35,986
Paper-wrapped bullet.

891
01:15:36,092 --> 01:15:38,617
No metal on metal
going down the barrel.

892
01:15:38,728 --> 01:15:41,754
Grooves would match.
Paper unwinds at the muzzle.

893
01:15:41,865 --> 01:15:43,890
Leaves no traces when it hits.

894
01:15:44,000 --> 01:15:47,629
Interesting question, though.
Hope I satisfied you.

895
01:15:47,737 --> 01:15:49,034
I got another one.

896
01:15:49,773 --> 01:15:50,797
I thought you might.

897
01:15:50,907 --> 01:15:53,899
Suppose I was looking for a man
to make a 2,200-yard cold-bore shot.

898
01:15:54,010 --> 01:15:55,705
Who's alive that could do that?

899
01:15:56,279 --> 01:16:00,409
Seems I heard about a shot like that
being made not too long ago.

900
01:16:00,517 --> 01:16:03,645
Said the guy's name
was Bob Lee Swagger.

901
01:16:03,753 --> 01:16:05,981
Never met the man,
so I wouldn't know him.

902
01:16:06,089 --> 01:16:07,556
Yeah, they said that, all right.

903
01:16:07,657 --> 01:16:11,354
They also said
that artificial sweeteners were safe,

904
01:16:12,362 --> 01:16:14,887
and WMDs were in Iraq,

905
01:16:14,998 --> 01:16:17,660
and Anna Nicole married for love!

906
01:16:19,636 --> 01:16:21,501
Would've been
a bad job to take, though.

907
01:16:21,605 --> 01:16:22,663
How come?

908
01:16:22,772 --> 01:16:25,332
Whoever took that shot's
probably dead now.

909
01:16:25,442 --> 01:16:27,342
That's how a conspiracy works.

910
01:16:27,444 --> 01:16:31,073
Them boys on the grassy knoll,
they were dead within three hours.

911
01:16:31,181 --> 01:16:35,117
Buried in the damn desert.
Unmarked graves out past Terlingua.

912
01:16:35,218 --> 01:16:36,651
And you know this for a fact?

913
01:16:36,753 --> 01:16:38,550
Still got the shovel.

914
01:16:40,724 --> 01:16:42,555
Sake of argument,
somebody other than him?

915
01:16:42,659 --> 01:16:44,183
There was a guy in Russia.

916
01:16:44,294 --> 01:16:46,057
They locked his ass up.

917
01:16:46,763 --> 01:16:49,425
Another one in France.
I know he's dead.

918
01:16:50,333 --> 01:16:52,198
There was one guy,

919
01:16:52,302 --> 01:16:54,566
but he don't shoot no more.

920
01:16:54,938 --> 01:16:57,702
A brutal son of a bitch.

921
01:16:57,807 --> 01:17:00,935
Most boys shoot to kill.
He'd shoot to wound,

922
01:17:01,678 --> 01:17:03,373
wait till his friends come to help,

923
01:17:03,780 --> 01:17:04,940
kill them too.

924
01:17:05,048 --> 01:17:07,209
Turned one target into four.

925
01:17:07,984 --> 01:17:11,715
Men, women, children.
Killed them by the hundreds.

926
01:17:11,821 --> 01:17:14,085
The other side wanted him. Bad.

927
01:17:14,190 --> 01:17:19,492
Finally narrowed his hide down
to an abandoned six-story building.

928
01:17:20,697 --> 01:17:22,631
They quit the subtle tactics.

929
01:17:22,732 --> 01:17:25,360
They called in an artillery strike.

930
01:17:25,468 --> 01:17:27,368
Leveled a square block.

931
01:17:27,470 --> 01:17:29,631
Brought the building down on his ass.

932
01:17:29,739 --> 01:17:32,173
Some say he crawled out of there.

933
01:17:32,275 --> 01:17:34,004
Some say he died.

934
01:17:34,110 --> 01:17:36,044
Never heard from him no more.

935
01:17:36,746 --> 01:17:38,304
Fuck me.

936
01:17:38,415 --> 01:17:39,404
What?

937
01:17:39,516 --> 01:17:40,949
I met the son of a bitch.

938
01:17:45,422 --> 01:17:48,448
Yeah. The world ain't what it seems,
is it, Gunnie?

939
01:17:49,426 --> 01:17:50,552
No, sir.

940
01:17:50,660 --> 01:17:52,252
You keep that in mind.

941
01:17:52,362 --> 01:17:54,125
The moment you think you got it figured,

942
01:17:54,297 --> 01:17:55,264
you're wrong.

943
01:17:59,336 --> 01:18:00,394
He got a name?

944
01:18:05,909 --> 01:18:07,342
Hey, it's me, Nick.

945
01:18:07,444 --> 01:18:10,379
Do you have any idea
how much trouble you're in?

946
01:18:11,114 --> 01:18:13,105
- Yeah.
- Are you okay? Nick, where are you?

947
01:18:13,216 --> 01:18:14,444
It's better I don't tell you.

948
01:18:15,285 --> 01:18:17,651
Look, do you have a pen?

949
01:18:17,754 --> 01:18:20,222
I need you to find someone.
Mikhaylo Sczerbiak.

950
01:18:20,323 --> 01:18:21,290
- Yeah.
- You got it?

951
01:18:21,391 --> 01:18:22,380
I got it.

952
01:18:22,525 --> 01:18:24,356
Man, this is hard to spell.

953
01:18:30,567 --> 01:18:33,730
Swagger is going to go
with what he knows.

954
01:18:33,837 --> 01:18:36,101
He'll try to track the shooter.

955
01:18:36,206 --> 01:18:37,730
He won't get far that way.

956
01:18:37,841 --> 01:18:39,331
Yes, he will.

957
01:18:39,442 --> 01:18:41,535
- How's that?
- We're going to help him.

958
01:18:41,644 --> 01:18:44,704
Sometimes to catch a wolf,
you need to tie the bait to a tree.

959
01:18:51,855 --> 01:18:53,550
And what happens to the bait?

960
01:18:55,091 --> 01:18:56,456
Hard to say.

961
01:18:57,460 --> 01:19:00,122
But that's the nature of being the bait.

962
01:19:13,176 --> 01:19:15,542
- Hey, it's Nick. Did you find him?
- He's in Virginia.

963
01:19:16,613 --> 01:19:18,706
An end we thought was tied up

964
01:19:18,915 --> 01:19:20,007
came untied.

965
01:19:20,950 --> 01:19:22,611
Meaning, Colonel?

966
01:19:22,719 --> 01:19:24,550
Swagger is still alive.

967
01:19:27,991 --> 01:19:29,356
Oh, my.

968
01:19:29,993 --> 01:19:34,623
I need to land a transport plane
without a customs check.

969
01:19:36,299 --> 01:19:39,894
I'm certain I don't want to know,
but what's on the plane?

970
01:19:41,704 --> 01:19:43,467
Crew we used in Ethiopia.

971
01:19:43,573 --> 01:19:46,565
Twenty-four good, hard men.

972
01:19:46,676 --> 01:19:48,837
Weapons and gear.

973
01:19:48,945 --> 01:19:50,469
Only 24?

974
01:19:51,915 --> 01:19:53,314
Do kill him.

975
01:19:55,051 --> 01:19:56,985
No loose ends this time.

976
01:19:57,887 --> 01:19:59,286
Night, Colonel.

977
01:20:00,957 --> 01:20:01,946
Good night, Senator.

978
01:20:20,810 --> 01:20:21,868
Hello?

979
01:20:24,080 --> 01:20:25,479
Someone there?

980
01:21:01,751 --> 01:21:02,877
Now look.

981
01:21:03,586 --> 01:21:05,383
Look what you've done now.

982
01:21:08,658 --> 01:21:10,091
Give me that.

983
01:21:10,193 --> 01:21:13,185
I don't want you to hurt yourself. Okay?

984
01:21:21,704 --> 01:21:23,535
Where's your boyfriend?

985
01:21:25,775 --> 01:21:27,367
What if it's a trap?

986
01:21:27,810 --> 01:21:29,175
Oh, it's a trap.

987
01:21:29,279 --> 01:21:31,611
Guaranteed. Every time.

988
01:21:33,483 --> 01:21:35,178
Question is, for whom?

989
01:21:36,686 --> 01:21:38,517
- You got your list, right?
- Yep.

990
01:21:38,621 --> 01:21:40,851
All right, you make sure you stick to it.

991
01:22:08,918 --> 01:22:09,885
Let's go.

992
01:22:15,425 --> 01:22:17,450
Okay, so what are these for again?

993
01:22:18,161 --> 01:22:19,856
Tear gas is going to be on my remote.

994
01:22:19,963 --> 01:22:21,521
Right.

995
01:22:21,631 --> 01:22:25,863
Napalm on the first floor.
Pipe bombs on the rest of them.

996
01:22:25,969 --> 01:22:29,996
Gotta be very careful with these.
It's got a 15-foot kill radius.

997
01:22:30,106 --> 01:22:32,267
So what exactly
are we getting ready for?

998
01:22:32,375 --> 01:22:33,808
For as much as we can be.

999
01:22:46,956 --> 01:22:49,186
All right, you got
four enemy combatants.

1000
01:22:49,292 --> 01:22:51,021
Take them one by one.

1001
01:22:51,127 --> 01:22:53,061
Keep shooting.
Don't let anything distract you.

1002
01:23:01,671 --> 01:23:02,729
Fuck!

1003
01:23:05,041 --> 01:23:07,475
Didn't I say
don't let anything distract you?

1004
01:23:07,577 --> 01:23:10,102
Slow is smooth, smooth is fast.
Let's see it.

1005
01:23:26,195 --> 01:23:27,719
No. No.

1006
01:23:28,264 --> 01:23:30,095
It's just you and me, baby.

1007
01:23:30,199 --> 01:23:31,257
No!

1008
01:23:34,337 --> 01:23:35,804
You got three guards.

1009
01:23:36,706 --> 01:23:38,139
One at your 2:00,

1010
01:23:39,542 --> 01:23:40,634
12:00

1011
01:23:42,011 --> 01:23:43,137
and 10:00.

1012
01:23:51,754 --> 01:23:52,778
Danger close. 2:00,

1013
01:23:52,889 --> 01:23:53,856
fifty yards.

1014
01:24:57,487 --> 01:24:58,545
You got one right on you.

1015
01:24:58,988 --> 01:24:59,955
20 yards and closing.

1016
01:25:50,673 --> 01:25:52,072
Go check the perimeter.

1017
01:25:52,508 --> 01:25:54,032
And tell the others to stay alert.

1018
01:25:54,143 --> 01:25:55,872
I'm on it. Right away, sir.

1019
01:26:30,046 --> 01:26:31,536
Swagger, you got one above you
on the roof.

1020
01:26:50,266 --> 01:26:51,563
You killed all three?

1021
01:26:52,502 --> 01:26:53,833
There were four.

1022
01:26:54,770 --> 01:26:58,228
I want Johnson's real name.
I want to know who he works for.

1023
01:26:58,341 --> 01:27:00,206
I want to know why it was worth
going through that much effort

1024
01:27:00,309 --> 01:27:01,742
to kill the Archbishop.

1025
01:27:02,678 --> 01:27:04,168
Aren't you the one that shot him?

1026
01:27:04,280 --> 01:27:06,339
And if I don't know any of those things?

1027
01:27:06,449 --> 01:27:07,541
Then you're of no worth to me

1028
01:27:07,650 --> 01:27:09,811
and I might as well shoot you now
and leave.

1029
01:27:14,023 --> 01:27:16,423
Johnson's had a lot of names.

1030
01:27:16,526 --> 01:27:20,292
Don't know one's any more real
than the next.

1031
01:27:20,396 --> 01:27:22,125
Knowing would only be dangerous.

1032
01:27:23,799 --> 01:27:25,323
He's ex-army.

1033
01:27:25,434 --> 01:27:27,868
Pretty sure he was a full-bird colonel.

1034
01:27:31,173 --> 01:27:32,265
Go on.

1035
01:27:34,110 --> 01:27:36,874
They came for me,
like they came for you.

1036
01:27:38,047 --> 01:27:40,447
Recruitment for a single job.

1037
01:27:42,151 --> 01:27:43,584
They like the wounded.

1038
01:27:44,687 --> 01:27:46,348
Easier to use

1039
01:27:47,390 --> 01:27:49,358
and then throw away
when you are done.

1040
01:27:50,760 --> 01:27:52,751
Timmons, you, me...

1041
01:27:55,398 --> 01:28:00,335
Once you've been a wolf, it's hard
to be staked down like a goat.

1042
01:28:01,437 --> 01:28:06,204
This is just one dead man
talking to another.

1043
01:28:07,276 --> 01:28:08,607
And the Archbishop?

1044
01:28:10,246 --> 01:28:14,080
You want to take all suspicions away
when you shoot someone,

1045
01:28:14,350 --> 01:28:16,750
wait till he's standing
next to the President.

1046
01:28:18,187 --> 01:28:19,620
What was he going to say?

1047
01:28:20,656 --> 01:28:21,987
The truth.

1048
01:28:22,091 --> 01:28:25,652
That nothing, no matter how horrible,

1049
01:28:25,761 --> 01:28:29,253
ever really happens
without the approval of the government.

1050
01:28:29,365 --> 01:28:31,356
Over there, and here.

1051
01:28:33,469 --> 01:28:35,266
The problem isn't the doing.

1052
01:28:36,772 --> 01:28:38,865
It's the people in power having to admit

1053
01:28:39,342 --> 01:28:40,434
that they knew.

1054
01:28:42,211 --> 01:28:45,009
The prisoners are tortured
at Abu Ghraib,

1055
01:28:45,114 --> 01:28:47,275
and only the underlings go to jail.

1056
01:28:48,017 --> 01:28:49,609
Their bosses knew.

1057
01:28:49,719 --> 01:28:51,846
We know their bosses knew.

1058
01:28:51,954 --> 01:28:53,182
But you don't say it.

1059
01:28:53,289 --> 01:28:55,018
What exactly happened in Africa?

1060
01:28:55,124 --> 01:28:57,615
Somehow the villagers didn't think

1061
01:28:57,860 --> 01:28:59,760
that an oil pipeline

1062
01:29:00,363 --> 01:29:03,127
was a good enough reason
to move their village

1063
01:29:03,232 --> 01:29:06,668
to a place
where the spirit gods didn't exist.

1064
01:29:06,769 --> 01:29:07,736
Drink?

1065
01:29:07,837 --> 01:29:08,895
So they asked them all nicely to move

1066
01:29:09,005 --> 01:29:10,370
and when they didn't,
they just killed them all?

1067
01:29:10,473 --> 01:29:11,440
No.

1068
01:29:11,674 --> 01:29:12,902
They didn't ask.

1069
01:29:13,275 --> 01:29:14,640
They just killed them.

1070
01:29:14,744 --> 01:29:15,711
All.

1071
01:29:15,978 --> 01:29:18,947
So the next village
won't need to be asked.

1072
01:29:19,048 --> 01:29:20,379
They'll just go.

1073
01:29:32,194 --> 01:29:36,426
There is a mass grave with 400 bodies,

1074
01:29:36,532 --> 01:29:40,229
men, women, children,

1075
01:29:40,336 --> 01:29:44,966
under the oil pumping station
10 kilometers over the Eritrean border.

1076
01:29:46,742 --> 01:29:48,175
You should know.

1077
01:29:48,277 --> 01:29:52,304
You covered the retreat
of the contractors who did the job.

1078
01:29:53,683 --> 01:29:56,447
Of course, you weren't supposed
to survive that, either.

1079
01:30:05,594 --> 01:30:06,754
Who runs Johnson?

1080
01:30:06,862 --> 01:30:09,255
A senator. From Montana, I think.

1081
01:30:10,833 --> 01:30:12,460
You don't get it.

1082
01:30:12,902 --> 01:30:14,995
There is no head to cut off.

1083
01:30:16,172 --> 01:30:17,969
It's a conglomerate.

1084
01:30:18,607 --> 01:30:21,371
If one of them betrays the principles

1085
01:30:22,878 --> 01:30:25,108
of the accrual of money and power,

1086
01:30:26,215 --> 01:30:27,910
the others betray him.

1087
01:30:29,018 --> 01:30:30,542
What it is

1088
01:30:32,822 --> 01:30:35,120
is human weakness.

1089
01:30:36,492 --> 01:30:39,393
You can't kill that with a gun.

1090
01:30:47,303 --> 01:30:48,270
Swagger.

1091
01:30:48,370 --> 01:30:49,359
Swagger.

1092
01:30:49,472 --> 01:30:52,270
You got to get out of there.
They're everywhere.

1093
01:30:53,075 --> 01:30:56,169
Had to keep you till they got here.

1094
01:30:57,646 --> 01:31:00,945
Lying wasn't going to hold you.

1095
01:31:01,717 --> 01:31:03,275
You would have known.

1096
01:31:08,257 --> 01:31:11,556
By the way, they've got your woman.

1097
01:31:14,630 --> 01:31:15,688
Swagger.

1098
01:31:15,798 --> 01:31:19,256
They're 20 yards and closing.
You got to get out of there.

1099
01:31:21,036 --> 01:31:22,936
- Bug out. Go to hide two.
- Roger that.

1100
01:31:55,004 --> 01:31:56,665
Swagger, I'm in position two.

1101
01:31:57,573 --> 01:31:58,699
You got to get out of there.

1102
01:31:58,808 --> 01:32:00,275
- They're all over the place.
- Hey!

1103
01:32:00,876 --> 01:32:02,275
Calm down.

1104
01:32:02,378 --> 01:32:04,869
Blow the pipe bombs outside on my call,
okay? You got it?

1105
01:32:05,181 --> 01:32:06,978
Yeah, yeah. Yeah, I got it.

1106
01:32:14,557 --> 01:32:15,524
Listen very carefully.

1107
01:32:15,691 --> 01:32:17,318
On my one, you blow the pipe bombs,

1108
01:32:17,426 --> 01:32:18,393
then the gas.

1109
01:32:19,428 --> 01:32:21,191
Three, two, one...

1110
01:32:51,093 --> 01:32:52,219
Hit it. Hit the napalm.

1111
01:33:47,349 --> 01:33:48,338
Swagger!

1112
01:33:55,591 --> 01:33:56,888
You got it.

1113
01:34:08,237 --> 01:34:09,397
Swagger!

1114
01:34:11,807 --> 01:34:13,365
Swagger!

1115
01:34:14,076 --> 01:34:15,407
Swagger!

1116
01:34:22,017 --> 01:34:23,882
You got to bug out
on my go behind that barn.

1117
01:34:23,986 --> 01:34:24,953
Okay.

1118
01:34:25,054 --> 01:34:26,112
- You ready?
- Yeah.

1119
01:34:26,221 --> 01:34:27,245
Go!

1120
01:34:30,726 --> 01:34:31,693
Come on!

1121
01:35:00,122 --> 01:35:01,384
You got to gun it to that tree line.

1122
01:35:01,690 --> 01:35:02,657
What?

1123
01:35:02,825 --> 01:35:04,690
You got five shots left.
Gotta draw that bird out.

1124
01:35:04,793 --> 01:35:06,124
Okay. Okay.

1125
01:35:06,228 --> 01:35:08,093
- On my cover, all right?
- Okay.

1126
01:35:09,865 --> 01:35:10,854
All right, go!

1127
01:35:24,279 --> 01:35:25,769
Pull up! Pull up!

1128
01:35:41,830 --> 01:35:42,819
Time to go!

1129
01:36:00,716 --> 01:36:01,648
Let me take a look.

1130
01:36:02,084 --> 01:36:03,051
Not right now.

1131
01:36:03,652 --> 01:36:04,949
Morning, beautiful.

1132
01:36:05,054 --> 01:36:07,284
- See this weird shootout in Virginia?
- Sir...

1133
01:36:07,389 --> 01:36:11,723
Shells everywhere, helicopter remnants,
blood. No bodies, though, right?

1134
01:36:11,827 --> 01:36:15,456
And they get fingerprints
off the cartridge cases.

1135
01:36:15,564 --> 01:36:18,795
First set positively IDed
as Bob Lee Swagger.

1136
01:36:20,602 --> 01:36:24,038
Second set belongs
to Special Agent Nick Memphis

1137
01:36:24,506 --> 01:36:25,905
of the FBI.

1138
01:36:26,208 --> 01:36:27,732
What? That's gotta be wrong.

1139
01:36:31,080 --> 01:36:34,538
Now, the only reasonable question
to ask after that is,

1140
01:36:36,919 --> 01:36:38,147
what the fuck is going on?

1141
01:36:44,159 --> 01:36:45,490
Great shot!

1142
01:36:49,031 --> 01:36:51,556
- All yours, Dan!
- Good shooting!

1143
01:36:51,667 --> 01:36:54,932
I'm beginning to think that you were
the wrong man for the job.

1144
01:36:56,538 --> 01:36:58,005
Think what you want.

1145
01:37:00,542 --> 01:37:04,501
It appears we misjudged
the gunnery sergeant.

1146
01:37:06,315 --> 01:37:08,306
There's always a confused soul

1147
01:37:08,417 --> 01:37:11,011
that thinks that one man
can make a difference.

1148
01:37:12,187 --> 01:37:15,315
And you have to kill him
to convince him otherwise.

1149
01:37:17,659 --> 01:37:19,628
That's the hassle with democracy.

1150
01:37:20,129 --> 01:37:21,153
Pull!

1151
01:37:35,511 --> 01:37:37,445
...fire under their asses,
you understand me?

1152
01:37:37,546 --> 01:37:39,104
We need those results now.

1153
01:37:39,214 --> 01:37:41,546
Anna, you guys, you take the team...
Anna!... to the roadhouse.

1154
01:37:41,650 --> 01:37:44,244
Okay, I don't care who it is right now.
I don't give...

1155
01:37:44,353 --> 01:37:47,516
Guys! We got Memphis on the line.

1156
01:37:47,623 --> 01:37:48,851
Start a trace.

1157
01:37:49,758 --> 01:37:51,350
Got it. I'm on it.

1158
01:37:51,460 --> 01:37:53,690
Nick. Hey, it's Howard here.
How are you?

1159
01:37:53,962 --> 01:37:57,090
Things have gotten a little complicated.
I got Bob Lee Swagger in custody.

1160
01:37:58,200 --> 01:38:00,134
Yeah, turns out he's not dead, Howard.

1161
01:38:00,235 --> 01:38:02,829
Yeah, I know. Word of that possibility
had begun to reach us.

1162
01:38:03,572 --> 01:38:04,800
Got him.

1163
01:38:04,907 --> 01:38:06,534
Were you in a gunfight
in Virginia last night?

1164
01:38:06,642 --> 01:38:09,440
Like I said,
things have gotten a little complicated.

1165
01:38:09,545 --> 01:38:13,914
Well, obviously the best thing for you
would be to bring him in, right?

1166
01:38:14,016 --> 01:38:15,916
Oh, no. I can't do that.

1167
01:38:16,018 --> 01:38:17,007
Why?

1168
01:38:17,119 --> 01:38:19,110
It's gotten too deep.
It's not clear who can be trusted.

1169
01:38:20,022 --> 01:38:22,388
- But we're the FBI, son.
- Yeah, I know.

1170
01:38:22,791 --> 01:38:23,917
Yeah, I'll keep in touch.

1171
01:38:24,226 --> 01:38:25,318
Oh, Nick, wait...

1172
01:38:25,427 --> 01:38:27,327
Son of a bitch.

1173
01:38:27,429 --> 01:38:28,453
- Did we get that?
- Got him.

1174
01:38:28,564 --> 01:38:29,656
- Let's move.
- They're on an interstate

1175
01:38:29,765 --> 01:38:31,995
- outside Bozeman, Montana.
- Let's move!

1176
01:38:37,773 --> 01:38:38,740
This is Swagger.

1177
01:38:38,840 --> 01:38:40,535
- Colonel Johnson here.
- Figured you'd be listening.

1178
01:38:40,642 --> 01:38:43,042
- It appears you have nowhere to go.
- Colonel?

1179
01:38:43,579 --> 01:38:44,546
If it is "Colonel"?

1180
01:38:44,980 --> 01:38:46,106
It is.

1181
01:38:47,616 --> 01:38:50,642
- I have something you want.
- Well, it seems so do I.

1182
01:38:53,722 --> 01:38:58,489
Over the Eritrean border,
there is a mass grave with 400 bodies.

1183
01:38:58,594 --> 01:39:01,290
Men, women, children.

1184
01:39:02,464 --> 01:39:04,398
Tell you what, I'll give it to you
and we'll call it even.

1185
01:39:04,499 --> 01:39:05,966
I just want someone there I can trust.

1186
01:39:06,068 --> 01:39:08,662
I'm amenable.
Who do you have in mind?

1187
01:39:08,770 --> 01:39:10,670
How about that guy from U2
with the glasses?

1188
01:39:10,772 --> 01:39:13,172
Friend of Nelson Mandela and all.
He seems trustworthy.

1189
01:39:13,275 --> 01:39:15,266
Bono? You want them to get Bono?

1190
01:39:15,377 --> 01:39:18,710
My colleague's questioning
my choice. Okay,

1191
01:39:18,814 --> 01:39:22,306
I see how that could be a tough
problem. You know, last minute and all.

1192
01:39:23,285 --> 01:39:25,082
How about six-term senator
Charles Meachum

1193
01:39:25,387 --> 01:39:26,615
from Montana?

1194
01:39:26,722 --> 01:39:29,555
Seems like a pretty good
second choice, don't you think?

1195
01:39:31,326 --> 01:39:32,588
I don't think so.

1196
01:39:32,694 --> 01:39:35,561
I'm gonna provide you
with two numbers, then we'll talk.

1197
01:39:35,664 --> 01:39:38,292
Point 732. Point 648.

1198
01:39:38,834 --> 01:39:40,028
And what the hell is that?

1199
01:39:40,135 --> 01:39:43,298
Those are the last three digits, down to
a few meters of latitude and longitude,

1200
01:39:43,405 --> 01:39:45,396
of an oil pipeline pumping station
in Eritrea

1201
01:39:45,507 --> 01:39:46,838
with 400 bodies underneath.

1202
01:39:47,542 --> 01:39:48,736
Where are we meeting?

1203
01:39:50,412 --> 01:39:52,505
Somewhere I can see you,

1204
01:39:53,582 --> 01:39:56,346
coming from a goddamn long way off.

1205
01:41:04,853 --> 01:41:06,184
Where's your boy?

1206
01:41:20,569 --> 01:41:22,196
Well, I'm here.

1207
01:41:31,012 --> 01:41:32,036
He's here.

1208
01:41:32,147 --> 01:41:33,444
Look, look, look.

1209
01:41:34,282 --> 01:41:36,307
There's your boy.
There's your boy, baby.

1210
01:41:44,993 --> 01:41:47,086
Come on, come on. Look, look. Look up.

1211
01:41:57,372 --> 01:41:58,669
Okay.

1212
01:42:42,217 --> 01:42:43,844
I think I broke a rib!

1213
01:42:45,487 --> 01:42:46,681
Don't move!

1214
01:42:47,122 --> 01:42:48,555
Is there anybody else?

1215
01:42:49,157 --> 01:42:50,124
No.

1216
01:43:17,052 --> 01:43:19,680
He head-shoots me, spasm kills her!

1217
01:43:20,989 --> 01:43:22,980
You got no shot!

1218
01:43:23,091 --> 01:43:26,492
No shot, Swagger!
You hear that, Swagger?

1219
01:43:29,264 --> 01:43:30,959
You got no shot!

1220
01:43:31,600 --> 01:43:34,398
What are you gonna do? Come on!

1221
01:43:43,378 --> 01:43:45,039
It's over for you, buddy!

1222
01:43:50,085 --> 01:43:52,713
No shot! Okay, fuck him.

1223
01:44:06,735 --> 01:44:08,259
Not bad!

1224
01:44:08,370 --> 01:44:10,565
Pretty good! He went for the shot.

1225
01:44:13,008 --> 01:44:14,134
Christ.

1226
01:44:31,993 --> 01:44:33,085
How can we help you?

1227
01:44:33,194 --> 01:44:35,355
Guest at the motel last night
gave me $100

1228
01:44:35,463 --> 01:44:37,260
to bring this by here at 3:00 p.m.

1229
01:44:41,136 --> 01:44:42,125
Let's move!

1230
01:45:11,032 --> 01:45:12,021
You all right?

1231
01:45:12,834 --> 01:45:13,801
Yeah.

1232
01:45:24,179 --> 01:45:25,146
Search him.

1233
01:45:25,246 --> 01:45:26,804
I don't carry a weapon,

1234
01:45:29,818 --> 01:45:31,046
ordinarily.

1235
01:45:31,620 --> 01:45:33,747
I'm licensed to carry that in this state.

1236
01:45:41,763 --> 01:45:43,060
Pull the pilot.

1237
01:45:44,666 --> 01:45:46,759
Put your weapon down! Put it down!

1238
01:45:46,868 --> 01:45:48,028
Put your gun down!

1239
01:45:48,136 --> 01:45:49,262
Easy. Easy.

1240
01:45:59,714 --> 01:46:00,772
Sarah.

1241
01:46:01,816 --> 01:46:03,443
Give me the gun.

1242
01:46:04,152 --> 01:46:05,915
It's okay. Give me the gun.

1243
01:46:15,263 --> 01:46:16,457
You okay?

1244
01:46:16,631 --> 01:46:19,225
Put them up. Keep them up.

1245
01:46:19,334 --> 01:46:20,892
Nice shooting, Gunnie.

1246
01:46:21,970 --> 01:46:24,564
Yeah, you got what you came for.

1247
01:46:24,673 --> 01:46:26,937
I think it's time you owe us
your side of the bargain.

1248
01:46:27,042 --> 01:46:28,009
You do, huh?

1249
01:46:28,143 --> 01:46:31,135
Yes, I do, son. I certainly do.

1250
01:46:31,813 --> 01:46:34,805
Why don't we think about all this
that has gone on

1251
01:46:34,916 --> 01:46:36,679
just as a preamble?

1252
01:46:36,785 --> 01:46:38,650
You got any plans after this?

1253
01:46:39,320 --> 01:46:43,757
You have a rather unique skill set.
I'd be interested in offering you a job.

1254
01:46:43,858 --> 01:46:46,053
Work? For you?

1255
01:46:46,161 --> 01:46:49,927
It's not really as bad as it seems.
It's all gonna be done in any case.

1256
01:46:50,031 --> 01:46:53,592
You might as well be on the side
that gets you well paid for your efforts.

1257
01:46:53,702 --> 01:46:55,761
And what side are you on?

1258
01:46:55,870 --> 01:46:58,737
There are no sides.
There's no Sunnis and Shiites.

1259
01:46:58,840 --> 01:47:00,000
There's no Democrats and Republicans.

1260
01:47:00,108 --> 01:47:02,406
There's only haves and have-nots.

1261
01:47:02,510 --> 01:47:05,502
What exactly does working for you
entail, Senator?

1262
01:47:05,914 --> 01:47:09,111
Raping and murdering innocent women
and children, you sick fuck?

1263
01:47:09,217 --> 01:47:11,048
You sanctioned the mass murder
of an entire village

1264
01:47:11,152 --> 01:47:12,141
so a pipeline could go through.

1265
01:47:12,253 --> 01:47:13,845
One village!

1266
01:47:13,955 --> 01:47:15,980
And it brought stability to the region.

1267
01:47:16,091 --> 01:47:19,254
Which means that no one
chops off their arms

1268
01:47:19,360 --> 01:47:21,157
because their
grandmother's grandfather

1269
01:47:21,262 --> 01:47:22,854
belonged to a different tribe.

1270
01:47:23,865 --> 01:47:25,355
They like us down there, boy.

1271
01:47:32,407 --> 01:47:34,500
This is a country

1272
01:47:35,243 --> 01:47:37,438
where the Secretary of Defense

1273
01:47:39,614 --> 01:47:41,206
can go on TV

1274
01:47:41,583 --> 01:47:43,710
and tell the American public,

1275
01:47:43,918 --> 01:47:47,547
oh, that "This is about freedom!
It's not about oil!"

1276
01:47:48,356 --> 01:47:50,290
And nobody questions him,

1277
01:47:50,391 --> 01:47:51,824
because they don't want to hear
the answer

1278
01:47:51,926 --> 01:47:53,257
because it's a lie!

1279
01:47:55,697 --> 01:47:59,929
There's only so many places
at the table, Gunnie.

1280
01:48:00,335 --> 01:48:01,996
Now are you on the inside,

1281
01:48:02,337 --> 01:48:03,634
or are you on the out?

1282
01:48:10,712 --> 01:48:12,043
It's the FBI!

1283
01:48:12,881 --> 01:48:14,473
It's gonna be okay. Hold this.

1284
01:48:17,218 --> 01:48:20,585
If one of them betrays
the principles of the accrual...

1285
01:48:20,688 --> 01:48:22,349
I don't think so, Senator.

1286
01:48:26,594 --> 01:48:28,528
- What are you doing?
- Saving our lives.

1287
01:48:28,963 --> 01:48:31,090
- That proved you were innocent!
- Nobody out here is innocent!

1288
01:48:31,199 --> 01:48:35,033
This stuff's plutonium.
Nobody can handle it without dying.

1289
01:48:35,136 --> 01:48:38,594
You hand it over to the authorities,
it's just gonna disappear, along with us!

1290
01:48:38,706 --> 01:48:41,698
Unless you want to get buried
in the hills outside Terlingua.

1291
01:48:41,810 --> 01:48:43,334
I'm out, old man!

1292
01:48:43,444 --> 01:48:46,242
I'm just a peckerwood who lives
in the hills with too many guns.

1293
01:48:46,347 --> 01:48:47,644
You happy?

1294
01:48:51,953 --> 01:48:53,716
Where do you think you're going?

1295
01:48:53,822 --> 01:48:55,255
Washington!

1296
01:48:55,356 --> 01:48:59,793
You going to shoot
a sitting U.S. senator in the back?

1297
01:48:59,894 --> 01:49:01,452
Lord knows I want to.

1298
01:49:02,330 --> 01:49:03,763
I didn't think so.

1299
01:49:05,033 --> 01:49:06,227
Let him go.

1300
01:49:07,268 --> 01:49:08,895
They've got your rifle.

1301
01:49:10,505 --> 01:49:12,939
From the beginning,
they've always had your rifle.

1302
01:49:13,041 --> 01:49:14,702
Recovered at the site.

1303
01:49:22,050 --> 01:49:24,712
You can talk as much as you want,
but in the end,

1304
01:49:25,186 --> 01:49:27,677
you're going to die by lethal injection,

1305
01:49:27,789 --> 01:49:30,280
and I'm going to go back
to what I was doing.

1306
01:49:35,496 --> 01:49:36,622
I won.

1307
01:49:37,665 --> 01:49:39,030
You lost.

1308
01:49:39,834 --> 01:49:41,995
Get used to the idea, son.

1309
01:49:42,470 --> 01:49:43,903
I'm not your son.

1310
01:49:58,553 --> 01:50:00,817
- Drop your weapons! Put it down now!
- Don't move!

1311
01:50:00,922 --> 01:50:04,483
Special Agent Nick Memphis, FBI!
Don't shoot!

1312
01:50:04,592 --> 01:50:06,753
- Down, now!
- On the ground!

1313
01:50:07,362 --> 01:50:08,386
I said get down!

1314
01:50:27,749 --> 01:50:30,377
- Could I free my hands, please?
- It's okay.

1315
01:50:30,485 --> 01:50:32,112
Thank you, sir.

1316
01:50:33,588 --> 01:50:35,249
Thanks for bringing her.

1317
01:50:40,795 --> 01:50:43,423
Hey. I'm sorry about everything.

1318
01:50:43,531 --> 01:50:45,829
It's not your fault. It is what it is.

1319
01:50:49,570 --> 01:50:52,198
This is Attorney General Russert.

1320
01:50:53,207 --> 01:50:55,801
- Director Brandt.
- Sir.

1321
01:50:55,910 --> 01:50:58,242
Senator Meachum couldn't be
with us today.

1322
01:50:58,346 --> 01:51:00,507
I'm sure we can manage without him.

1323
01:51:00,615 --> 01:51:02,844
Sergeant Swagger,
you asked for this meeting.

1324
01:51:03,918 --> 01:51:07,149
Against my better judgment,
I've agreed to it as a favor to the FBI.

1325
01:51:07,255 --> 01:51:08,722
What the hell am I doing here?

1326
01:51:08,957 --> 01:51:11,050
You've got nothing on me. I'm covered.

1327
01:51:11,526 --> 01:51:12,925
Call the Joint Chief.

1328
01:51:14,562 --> 01:51:15,859
That won't be necessary, Colonel,

1329
01:51:15,964 --> 01:51:18,330
as I have already received
no less than a dozen calls

1330
01:51:18,433 --> 01:51:20,901
from highly-ranked
and powerfully-placed individuals

1331
01:51:21,002 --> 01:51:22,492
telling me to let you go.

1332
01:51:22,603 --> 01:51:25,697
But the joy of checks and balances
in our government is that I can,

1333
01:51:26,641 --> 01:51:28,108
and am, indeed, required by law,

1334
01:51:28,242 --> 01:51:30,437
to tell them to fuck off.

1335
01:51:30,545 --> 01:51:32,206
This is about evidence
and finding out the truth,

1336
01:51:32,313 --> 01:51:34,247
so you sit there and be quiet.

1337
01:51:37,885 --> 01:51:39,876
Sergeant, you've got five minutes.

1338
01:51:39,988 --> 01:51:41,114
Thank you.

1339
01:51:43,324 --> 01:51:45,053
This is my weapon.

1340
01:51:45,159 --> 01:51:47,491
No question about it, don't deny it.

1341
01:51:47,595 --> 01:51:49,961
You recovered it at the scene
moments after the assassination.

1342
01:51:50,064 --> 01:51:51,031
We agree?

1343
01:51:51,766 --> 01:51:53,290
It's been in the FBI's possession
ever since,

1344
01:51:53,401 --> 01:51:54,800
hasn't been tampered with in any way?

1345
01:51:54,902 --> 01:51:56,426
No. Absolutely not.

1346
01:51:56,537 --> 01:51:58,664
- You fire the weapon?
- There was no point.

1347
01:51:58,773 --> 01:52:00,934
The slug was mangled
beyond recognition.

1348
01:52:01,042 --> 01:52:03,943
It was, however,
an exact metallurgical match.

1349
01:52:04,045 --> 01:52:06,411
Right. Definitely my bullets.

1350
01:52:07,548 --> 01:52:09,209
Definitely my gun.

1351
01:52:09,317 --> 01:52:11,785
Special Agent Memphis,
you believe I shot that Archbishop?

1352
01:52:11,886 --> 01:52:13,410
Nope. No, I don't.

1353
01:52:13,521 --> 01:52:16,046
- Have any proof of this fact?
- No.

1354
01:52:16,157 --> 01:52:17,590
- Trust me?
- Yep.

1355
01:52:17,692 --> 01:52:18,852
Really trust me?

1356
01:52:19,227 --> 01:52:20,194
Yeah.

1357
01:52:21,262 --> 01:52:22,456
With your life?

1358
01:52:23,064 --> 01:52:24,463
- Yep.
- Good.

1359
01:52:26,034 --> 01:52:28,400
- What the hell are you doing?
- Put that weapon down now!

1360
01:52:28,503 --> 01:52:31,336
If you're zeroed for 600,
you ought to aim a little lower.

1361
01:52:31,439 --> 01:52:32,929
Ain't gonna make a difference
this close.

1362
01:52:33,041 --> 01:52:34,167
Only thing
that's gonna make a difference

1363
01:52:34,275 --> 01:52:35,799
is whether I'm crazy or not.

1364
01:52:42,216 --> 01:52:43,979
I could keep doing this all day,

1365
01:52:44,719 --> 01:52:46,311
with every weapon in my house.

1366
01:52:46,821 --> 01:52:49,881
I swapped all the firing pins
before I left the house. I always do.

1367
01:52:49,991 --> 01:52:52,016
Looks right, need a micrometer to tell.

1368
01:52:52,493 --> 01:52:53,858
But the gun don't shoot.

1369
01:52:54,262 --> 01:52:56,253
That bullet you got out of that bishop
was fired from my weapon,

1370
01:52:56,364 --> 01:52:58,127
but a week before, at a can of stew.

1371
01:52:58,232 --> 01:53:01,463
I did take an oath to defend this country
from all enemies, foreign and domestic.

1372
01:53:01,569 --> 01:53:03,867
I just didn't figure I'd end up
quite this involved.

1373
01:53:03,971 --> 01:53:05,734
But at the end of the day,
when all the dust settles,

1374
01:53:05,840 --> 01:53:08,400
you can't hide from the truth,
you son of a bitch.

1375
01:53:09,710 --> 01:53:10,836
Whatever.

1376
01:53:11,612 --> 01:53:13,079
Who gives a shit?

1377
01:53:14,415 --> 01:53:15,882
Nice presentation.

1378
01:53:15,983 --> 01:53:17,780
But none of it sticks to me.

1379
01:53:18,986 --> 01:53:22,183
Gentlemen, this meeting is over.

1380
01:53:22,290 --> 01:53:23,552
Done.

1381
01:53:23,658 --> 01:53:24,989
I'll be seeing you.

1382
01:53:25,093 --> 01:53:28,290
He's right. There's nothing
to prove he did anything.

1383
01:53:28,396 --> 01:53:29,590
Yeah, in this country.

1384
01:53:29,697 --> 01:53:32,325
Sir, you should take a look at these.

1385
01:53:37,738 --> 01:53:43,199
These images are from a classified file
showing a village of people in Africa

1386
01:53:43,311 --> 01:53:46,007
that were exterminated
by the colonel and his associates.

1387
01:53:46,114 --> 01:53:47,081
My God.

1388
01:53:47,281 --> 01:53:48,475
Look around you.

1389
01:53:49,050 --> 01:53:51,177
This isn't the Horn of Africa.

1390
01:53:51,285 --> 01:53:52,843
That's all hearsay.

1391
01:53:52,954 --> 01:53:55,582
This is the land of the free
and the home of the brave.

1392
01:53:55,690 --> 01:53:57,123
And I'm free to go.

1393
01:53:57,758 --> 01:53:59,555
Colonel, your moral compass is
so fucked up,

1394
01:53:59,660 --> 01:54:03,596
I'll be shocked if you manage
to find your way back to the parking lot.

1395
01:54:03,698 --> 01:54:05,825
Regardless of how I feel about this,

1396
01:54:06,868 --> 01:54:08,358
these events occurred
in another country,

1397
01:54:08,469 --> 01:54:09,766
outside of our laws.

1398
01:54:09,871 --> 01:54:12,396
So that's it? That's the best you can do?

1399
01:54:12,507 --> 01:54:14,532
This isn't the World Court, Sergeant.

1400
01:54:15,409 --> 01:54:17,707
And I don't have the jurisdiction
to detain the colonel

1401
01:54:17,812 --> 01:54:20,474
for crimes he may or may not have
committed on another continent.

1402
01:54:20,581 --> 01:54:24,108
- Sir, I urge you to reconsider...
- There's nothing to reconsider, son.

1403
01:54:27,588 --> 01:54:29,215
I win.

1404
01:54:29,323 --> 01:54:30,551
You lose.

1405
01:54:31,292 --> 01:54:32,259
Again.

1406
01:54:34,629 --> 01:54:36,187
This is ridiculous.

1407
01:54:58,486 --> 01:55:02,047
For the record, I don't like the way
this turned out any more than you do.

1408
01:55:02,757 --> 01:55:04,657
But this is the world we live in.

1409
01:55:04,759 --> 01:55:07,694
And justice does not always prevail.

1410
01:55:07,795 --> 01:55:08,762
It's not the Wild West,

1411
01:55:08,863 --> 01:55:11,161
where you can clean up the streets
with a gun.

1412
01:55:12,500 --> 01:55:15,333
Even though sometimes
that's exactly what's needed.

1413
01:55:19,974 --> 01:55:22,504
Bob Lee Swagger, you're free to go.

1414
01:55:26,647 --> 01:55:28,444
Unshackle the sergeant.

1415
01:55:31,786 --> 01:55:34,016
I'd say that's quite a shot, Senator.

1416
01:55:34,121 --> 01:55:35,383
In the face.

1417
01:55:36,791 --> 01:55:39,021
You heard that expression,

1418
01:55:39,126 --> 01:55:41,424
"You didn't know whether to shit
or go blind"?

1419
01:55:45,399 --> 01:55:48,630
You should've seen the look
on the Attorney General's face.

1420
01:55:49,737 --> 01:55:54,037
Did he give his
checks-and-balances speech?

1421
01:55:54,141 --> 01:55:57,542
"This is about evidence and the truth!"

1422
01:55:57,645 --> 01:56:00,170
And then you just said to him,

1423
01:56:00,281 --> 01:56:01,578
"Fuck you!"

1424
01:56:02,650 --> 01:56:05,050
"Hold my cigar, Mr. A.G."

1425
01:56:07,321 --> 01:56:08,618
"Fuck you!

1426
01:56:10,391 --> 01:56:12,825
"The truth is what I say it is!"

1427
01:56:19,900 --> 01:56:22,232
You know, you got to be
out of the country in the morning.

1428
01:56:22,336 --> 01:56:24,099
You're going to Ecuador.

1429
01:56:27,575 --> 01:56:31,170
Well, we're having some problems
with the locals.

1430
01:56:31,279 --> 01:56:34,840
We have our personnel on the ground
ready to neutralize the problem, but...

1431
01:56:35,116 --> 01:56:36,811
Well, they've requested you.

1432
01:56:38,586 --> 01:56:39,951
It's solvable.

1433
01:56:42,623 --> 01:56:43,817
They requested you...

1434
01:56:46,160 --> 01:56:47,184
Swagger.

1435
01:56:52,066 --> 01:56:53,124
Turn off the lights!

1436
01:57:00,708 --> 01:57:01,732
Get my car.

1437
01:57:01,909 --> 01:57:03,035
Get my car.

1438
01:57:22,897 --> 01:57:23,864
Do something.

1439
01:57:24,665 --> 01:57:25,893
Do something!

1440
01:57:34,208 --> 01:57:35,334
Where is he?

1441
01:57:48,022 --> 01:57:49,148
He's under the floor!

1442
01:58:19,954 --> 01:58:21,546
You don't need to kill me.

1443
01:58:22,890 --> 01:58:24,517
You don't need to kill me. It was them.

1444
01:58:24,959 --> 01:58:25,926
It was them.

1445
01:58:28,729 --> 01:58:31,493
God damn it! Just wait a minute!

1446
01:58:33,701 --> 01:58:36,101
Hold it just a minute. Hold it.

1447
01:58:38,439 --> 01:58:41,840
Are you out of your mind?
Are you out of your damn mind?

1448
01:58:41,942 --> 01:58:44,775
I am a United States senator!

1449
01:58:44,979 --> 01:58:45,947
Exactly.
